# Cursor Agent Instructions

This repository uses a structured multi-agent collaboration system. Before making any changes, understand your role and the rules that govern it.

## Quick Start

1. Read `/CLAUDE.md` for universal rules and the project index.
2. Identify your persona from `docs/agents/personas/`:
   - [Tech Lead](docs/agents/personas/tech-lead.md) -- technical plans, architecture, security (Phase 1 expanded)
   - [Acceptance Tester](docs/agents/personas/acceptance-tester.md) -- integration and E2E tests
   - [Developer](docs/agents/personas/developer.md) -- application code, CI, unit tests (Phase 1 expanded)
   - [Scrum Master](docs/agents/personas/scrum-master.md) -- process improvement, agent definitions
3. Read your persona definition for goals, constraints, and owned files.
4. Check `OWNERS.yaml` to confirm you can modify the files you intend to change.

## Key Rules

- **Read before writing.** Always read existing files before modifying them.
- **Respect ownership.** Only modify files within your persona's scope per `OWNERS.yaml`.
- **Follow the plan.** Check `.planning/plans/` for the current plan and work within its scope.
- **Small PRs.** Each PR corresponds to one planned PR unit.
- **Preserve patterns.** Match the style and conventions of existing code.
- **Validate before pushing.** Run `make validate-planning` for planning changes; run project-specific checks for code.

## Loop Workflows

See `docs/agents/loops/` for how agents collaborate:
- [Planning](docs/agents/loops/planning.md) -- ticket to technical plan
- [Verification](docs/agents/loops/verification.md) -- write failing acceptance tests (TDD)
- [Implementation](docs/agents/loops/implementation.md) -- build one planned PR
- [Accept](docs/agents/loops/accept.md) -- validate against acceptance criteria
- [Improve](docs/agents/loops/improve.md) -- retrospective and process improvements

## Context Extraction

Never read `.planning/` files in full. Use:
```
python3 scripts/planning/extract-context.py --persona <your-persona> --task <task-id>
```
